		<td><b>MMC1/3 H/V Mirroring</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I've hacked an old Guardian Legend cart, and managed to make an UNROM dev cart. I also added to it an H/V mirroring switch.
<br />Now I want to make a MMC1 cart and a MMC3 too!!!.
<br />After reading and searcing some of the topics, I found that these mappers makes the H/V mirroring through software. Its that correct?. It means I just can put any supported game in the carts without needing to select the mirroring through hardware, like in the UNROM cart, right?.
<br />Thanks in advance.
<br />Whipon.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>tepples</b> [ Wed May 14, 2008 8:58 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />With MMC1 and MMC3, instead of selecting mirroring, you have to select between CHR ROM and CHR RAM, or between PRG RAM at $6000 and open bus at $6000. Lose a wart, gain a wart.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

