	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />They are for reproductions. I like to hack the game code, like hacking it to have infinite lives, infinite health, and so on. I learned at GSHI.org
<br /><a href="http://www.gshi.org/?s=v2&amp;m=h&amp;sys=5&amp;hid=709" class="postlink">http://www.gshi.org/?s=v2&amp;m=h&amp;sys=5&amp;hid=709</a>
<br />And I've created lots of GG codes for NES.
<br />I'm not own a Game Genie nor an Action Replay. So I like to play the games with all the cheats hacked in the program code. I was doing something simillar with my Genesis and a Tototek cart. I couldn't do the same with NES, because the Powerpak allways is unavalaible and its very expensive. So I found this project at rahpnet:
<br /><a href="http://www.raphnet.net/electronique/nes_cart/nes_cart_en.php" class="postlink">http://www.raphnet.net/electronique/nes_cart/nes_cart_en.php</a>
<br />So I bought 4 AM29F040 EEPROMS, a Willem universal programmer and started the job. I fried 2 carts in the process, but the third try was a success.
<br />That way I created an UNROM dev cart.
<br />Now I wanted to do the same to play MMC1 and MMC3 games.
<br />So there's games like Megaman 6 that uses CHR RAM. And talking about MMC3 there's Captain Tsubasa Vol 2 that uses CHR ROM. Id love to have only one cartdidge for the two alternatives, but It would be very difficult, right?. Also I don''t have any schematics u_u.
<br />I'll start first with the MMC3 to play Captain Tsubasa Vol 2. n.n This game has 256 kb of PRG and 128 kb of CHR. So I only need to reproduce two times the PRG and four times the CHR, right? (the 29F040 has 512 kb).
<br />Thanks again <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" />.
<br />Whipon.[/url]

		

